    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.6.1" />
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UPTON SINCLAIR
                        <lb/>
                    PASADENA
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 22, 1919.</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am wondering if you would like me to send that letter to the "Appeal". They might care to print it. It could be changed into a letter to the "Appeal", instead of the <add>"P</add><del>p</del>ublic.<add>"</add></p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Sinclair</signed>
                    
                    <note>US:SD</note>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
